<statement><div><p>A tent is shaped like a triangular prism. The triangular ends of the tent each have a base of <m>{40}\, \text{cm}</m> and a height of <m>{21}\, \text{cm}</m>. The length of the tent is <m>{43}\, \text{cm}</m>. Calculate the total surface area of the tent’s canvas.</p>
<p><m>\text{Total surface area of the tent’s canvas}=</m><fillin characters="5" name="ans1"/><m>\,\text{cm}^2</m></p></div></statement>
<solution><div><p>
Given: A tent is shaped like a triangular prism with the following dimensions:
</p>
<p>
Base of right triangle <m>={20}\,\text{m}</m> <br/>
Height of triangle <m>={21}\,\text{m}</m> <br/>
Sloping side (hypotenuse) <m>={29}\,\text{m}</m> <br/>
Big base of tent <m>={40}\,\text{m}</m> <br/>
Length of tent <m>={43}\,\text{m}</m>
</p>

<p>
</p><ol type="a">
<li>
<p><alert>Find the Total Surface Area of the Tent</alert></p>

<p>
<m>\textbf{Step 1. Find the area of one triangular end}</m>
</p>
<p>
<md>
<mrow>A_{\triangle} \amp = \frac{1}{2} \times \text{base} \times \text{height}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{1}{2} \times {40} \times {21}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {420}\,\text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>
<m>\textbf{Step 2. Find the area of one rectangular side (the sloping panel)}</m>
</p>
<p>
<md>
<mrow>A_{\text{rect}} \amp = \text{sloping side} \times \text{length}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {29} \times {43}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {1247}\,\text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
</p>

<p>
<m>\textbf{Step 3. Find the total surface area of the tent’s canvas}</m>
</p>
<p>
<md>
<mrow>\text{Total Surface Area} \amp = 2(A_{\triangle}) + 2(A_{\text{rect}})</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = 2({420}) + 2({1247})</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = {3334}\,\text{m}^2</mrow>
</md>
</p>



<p>
<m>\boxed{\text{Total Surface Area of the Tent’s Canvas} = {3334}\,\text{m}^2}</m>
</p>

</li>
</ol>
</div></solution>
<answer><p><m>3334</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>